While in Moscow as private secretary to Ambassador Sir Frank Roberts, he was able to convey some information which helped US President John Kennedy understand the Russian position. While at the Foreign Office he worked on arms control.  Margaret Thatcher liked his style and sent him to Bonn, where he was widely admired by German diplomats. Born in London, he married Pascale Thierry-Mieg in 1961. He is survived by their son and three daughters. Christopher Mallaby born July 7, 1936 - Died February 28, 2022, aged 85 